    "extras": [
      "Cash still matters: carry small EUR or CAD/USD equivalents for casas, paladares, tips, and colectivos because card acceptance can disappear outside bigger hotels.",
      "Viazul seats can sell out several days ahead in dry season, so lock longer legs early and reconfirm departure points with your host the night before.",
      "Power cuts and patchy mobile data are common outside Havana and Varadero, so ask each casa about generator backup and download offline WhatsApp and map info.",
      "If Santiago feels too far for your timeframe, replace it with another Trinidad or Varadero night instead of forcing a 14+ hour bus sequence.",
      "Breakfast at casas is often excellent value in Cuba — usually fruit, eggs, bread, and coffee for less than a restaurant meal — so build it into your daily rhythm."
    ],
